notes: Max Homa won the Wells Fargo Championship for the second time (first since 2019), earning his fourth PGA TOUR title and second of the season. Homa became the second player to win the Wells Fargo Championship multiple times, joining Rory McIlroy.
The 2022 Wells Fargo Championship was played at TPC Potomac at Avenel Farm with the tournament moving for one year to accommodate the 2022 Presidents Cup at Quail Hollow Club.
Keegan Bradley entered the final round leading by two strokes before finishing T2.
McIlroy finished solo-fifth in his title defense.
